---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const currentPath = '/about';
---

<Layout title="About GSTAT Index Generation Tool" description="this tool is free browser-based software for creating professional court document bundle primarily for GSTAT E-filing. Learn about the tool, its author, and how it helps lawyers and litigants.">
	<Header currentPath={currentPath} />

	<main class="min-h-screen bg-gray-50">
		<!-- About Section -->
		<section class="py-12">
			<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
				<h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">About GSTAT Index Generation Tool</h1>

				<div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none space-y-6">
					<p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
						This tool does one job: Turning your documents into a proper GSTAT compliant court bundle.
					</p>

					<p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
						Bundles in court are important, because a court can't follow along with the evidence unless everyone is looking at the same thing. In 2025, <a href="https://www.civillitigationbrief.com/2025/04/22/three-versions-of-a-bundle-made-the-hearing-so-unfair-as-to-require-a-rehearing/" class="text-slate-700 hover:text-slate-900 underline font-medium" target="_blank" rel="noopener">a local authority's bundles were so bad that an entire case had to be re-heard</a>!
					</p>

					<p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
						Knowing what to put in and how to present them is a skill - but assembling them, paginating and bookmarking them is a pain. BunTool separates out the skill from the pain, letting people focus on their cases without needing to faff around with page numbering. The Court's rules can also be <a href="/guide#court-rules" class="text-slate-700 hover:text-slate-900 underline font-medium">difficult to follow</a>.
					</p>

					<p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
						It's designed to be very quick and very simple so that anyone can use it even if they've never been near a court before, and to run in a browser (like Firefox, Edge, Safari or Chrome) without needing to install any special programs. The bundles are quite convenient, and work well for other contexts too - like formal meetings, for example. And it's <strong>totally private</strong>.
					</p>

					<p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
						Since its first release, it has been used by court users of every kind: litigants in person, local authorities, pro bono advocacy and welfare charities, established law firms, and mediators and barristers in countries across the world.
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- About the Author Section -->
				<div class="mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-gray-200">
					<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">About the Author</h2>
					<div class="space-y-6">
						<!-- Profile Photo - Float Right -->
						<img src="/images/tris-med.png" alt="Tristan Sherliker" class="float-right ml-6 mb-4 rounded-lg w-48 h-auto" />

						<p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
							BunTool is developed by me, Tristan Sherliker. I'm an English lawyer*, and developer of small software tools. I enjoy technology and making tools for me and others to use. After working in the courts for over a decade with many inspirational people, BunTool started life as a quick bit of software to get the job of bundling done quickly. It became very useful, and I eventually extended it into something that anyone can use on their own computers.
						</p>

						<p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
							*Although I'm a lawyer on other days, BunTool is an entirely separate personal project released with my software developer hat on and is not a vehicle for legal advice. Please remember that this is free, open source software licensed without warranties.
						</p>

						<p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
							If you've found BunTool helpful, or encountered a problem, or have any ideas please <a href="mailto:tris@sherliker.net" class="text-slate-700 hover:text-slate-900 underline font-medium">drop me a line</a>.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<!-- Tools and use of AI Section -->
				<div id="tools-ai" class="mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-gray-200">
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Tools and use of AI</h2>
					<div class="space-y-4">
						<p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
							BunTool itself depends on many free software tools written by others, such as mupdf, jspdf, and pdf-lib. It would not be possible without the amazing work of their developers.
						</p>

						<p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
							BunTool is not AI generated - its processing functions are written and maintained by hand. The website design is however created with the aid of Claude AI, using the Astro static site generator - another amazing piece of free software.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<!-- Back to Home -->
				<div class="mt-12 text-center">
					<a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white font-semibold rounded-lg shadow-sm transition">
						← Back to Home
					</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>

	<Footer />
</Layout>
